Base.Explanation: Remove a permission of an Active Directory object. Like for example: a group, organizational unit, user or computer.

Base.Name: Identity
Base.Description: The Identity parameter identifies the Active Directory object (group, user, computer or organizational unit) you want to remove a permission from. Use for example the distinguished name (OU=sales,DC=tools4ever,DC=com), the domain\account name (tools4ever.com\Jsmith) or the GUID.

Base.Name: Account
Base.Description: The Account parameter identifies the user account or group of which you want to remove permissions of this Active Directory object from. Use for example the distinguished name (CN=jsmith,OU=sales,DC=tools4ever,DC=com), the domain\account name (tools4ever.com\Jsmith), the User principal name (UPN). (JSmith@tools4ever.com) or the GUID.

Base.Name: Access rights
Base.Description: The 'Access rights' parameter identifies the access rights you want to remove from the Active Directory object. Valid values are Delete, ReadControl, WriteDacl, WriteOwner, Synchronize, AccessSystemSecurity, GenericRead, GenericWrite, GenericExecute, GenericAll, CreateChild, DeleteChild, ListChildren, Self, ReadProperty, WriteProperty, DeleteTree, ListObject and ExtendedRight.

Base.Name: Extended rights
Base.Description: The 'Extended rights' parameter identifies the extended rights you want to remove from the Active Directory object. Valid values are Open-Address-Book, Allowed-To-Authenticate, Receive-As, Send-As, User-Change-Password, User-Force-Change-Password, Send-To, Apply-Group-Policy, Allowed-To-Authenticate and Enable-Per-User-Reversibly-Encrypted-Password.

Base.Name: Child object types
Base.Description: The 'Child object types' parameter specifies what type of object the permissions is with.

Base.Name: Inheritance type
Base.Description: The 'Inheritance type' parameter specifies whether permissions are inherited. Use for example: None, All, Descendents, SelfAndChildren or Children.

Base.Name: Inherited object type
Base.Description: The 'Inherited object type' parameter specifies what kind of object inherits this ACE. Use for example: User, Group, Computer etc.

Base.Name: Properties
Base.Description: The 'Properties' parameter specifies on what properties of the Active Directory object this ACE applies to. Use for example: E-mail-Addresses, Display-Name, Exchange-Information etc.

Base.Name: Deny
Base.Description: Set the 'Deny' parameter to 'Yes' to remove a deny permission for the specified account on this Active Directory object.

Base.Name: Domain controller
Base.Description: Optional value. The name of the domain controller used to retrieve the Active Directory object's permissions from. Use the fully qualified domain name (FQDN) of the domain controller you want to use. For example: EXCHSERVER.tools4ever.com.
